 BY AYO ESAN THE National Working Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party has extended the tenure of the Zonal Caretaker Committees of the party across the six geo-political zones, pending its March 6 Zonal Congresses. The party, in a release issued on Sunday, and signed by its National Publicity Secretary, Kola Ologbondiyan, said the decision of the National Working Committee was sequel to the expiration of the tenure of the various caretaker committees. Meanwhile, the party has also charged the North Central Zonal Caretaker Committee with the responsibility of overseeing the affairs and administration of the Niger State Chapter of the party, pending when its state congress would hold. The party urged all its leaders, members and teeming supporters to be guided by the directive accordingly. 